description: This header file declares external APIs related to the Daemon Socket TCP object, including creation, removal, enrollment, and initialization functions. It defines function prototypes to be used across different modules.

methods.name: AnscCreateDaemonSocketTcp
methods.description: Creates a new Daemon Socket TCP object with provided context handles.

methods.name: AnscDktoCreate
methods.description: Creates an instance of the Daemon Socket TCP object with provided context handles.

methods.name: AnscDktoRemove
methods.description: Removes the specified Daemon Socket TCP object instance.

methods.name: AnscDktoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects for the Daemon Socket TCP object.

methods.name: AnscDktoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the Daemon Socket TCP object.
